Compute
\[\prod_{n = 1}^{20} \frac{n + 3}{n}.\] ||| We have that\begin{align*}\prod_{n = 1}^{20} &= \frac{4}{1} \cdot \frac{5}{2} \cdot \frac{6}{3} \cdot \frac{7}{4} \dotsm \frac{20}{17} \cdot \frac{21}{18} \cdot \frac{22}{19} \cdot \frac{23}{20} \\
&= \frac{4 \cdot 5 \cdot 6 \cdots 23}{1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdots 20} = \frac{23!}{3!} = \boxed{1540}.\end{align*}

