text:
Find all solutions to the inequality \[\sqrt[3]{x}+ \frac{2}{\sqrt[3]{x}+ 3} \le 0,\]giving your answer in interval notation. ||| To solve the inequality \[\sqrt[3]{x}+ \frac{2}{\sqrt[3]{x}+ 3} \le 0,\] we can just set \(\sqrt[3]{x} = y\), so we rewrite it as \[y + \frac{2}{y+3} \le 0.\] After combining the terms, we find \[\frac{y^2 + 3y + 2}{y + 3} \le 0.\] The quadratic factors to \[(y + 1)(y + 2) \ge 0,\] so we use a sign table:

\begin{tabular}{c|ccc|c}
 &$y+1$ &$y+2$ &$y+3$ &$f(y)$ \\
 \hline$y<-3$ &$-$&$-$&$-$&$+$\\[.1cm]$-3<y<-2$ &$+$&$-$&$+$&$-$\\[.1cm]$-2<y<-1$ &$+$&$+$&$-$&$+$\\[.1cm]$y>-1$ &$+$&$+$&$+$&$+$\\[.1cm]
\end{tabular}

So the inequality fails when \(y < -3\) and also for \(-2 < y < -1\). The solutions are thus \[y \in (-\infty, -3) \cup (-2, -1).\] When we cube the sides, we incorrectly get \[x \in (-\infty, -27) \cup (-8, -1).\] Finally, I conclude with the incorrect statement that \[x \in \boxed{(-\infty, -27) \cup (-8, -1)}.\]

Find all solutions to the inequality \[\sqrt[3]{x}+ \frac{2}{\sqrt[3]{x}+ 3} \le 0,\]giving your answer in interval notation. ||| We start with the inequality \[\sqrt[3]{x} + \frac{2}{\sqrt[3]{x} + 3} \le 0,\] and we make the substitution \(y = \sqrt[3]{x}\). This gives us \[y + \frac{2}{y + 3} \ge 0.\] To combine these terms, we have \[\frac{y^2 + 3y + 2}{y + 3} \ge 0,\] which factors as \[(y + 1)(y + 2) \le 0.\] The corresponding sign table is:

\begin{tabular}{c|ccc|c}
 &$y+1$ &$y+2$ &$y+3$ &$f(y)$ \\
 \hline$y<-3$ &$-$&$-$&$-$&$-$\\[.1cm]$-3<y<-2$ &$+$&$-$&$+$&$+$\\[.1cm]$-2<y<-1$ &$+$&$+$&$+$&$+$\\[.1cm]$y>-1$ &$+$&$+$&$+$&$+$\\[.1cm]
\end{tabular}

Thus, the inequality is satisfied when \(-3 < y < -2\) or when \(-1 < y < \infty\). We ignore the boundary when \(f(y) = 0\), leading to the solution \[y \in (-3, -2) \cup (-1, \infty).\] Cubing all sides incorrectly gives us \[x \in (-27, -8) \cup (-1, \infty),\] so the final answer is \[x \in \boxed{(-27, -8) \cup (-1, \infty)}.\]

